HEADWORD: Ferreous
<hw>Fer"re*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ferreus</ets>, fr. <ets>ferrum</ets> iron. Cf. <er>Farrier</er>,
<er>Ferrous</er>.]</ety> <def>Partaking of, made of, or pertaining to,
iron; like iron.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
